commit_message:
Removing ORF code.

Going back to just having one exercise. I'll create a separate
repo for multiple exercises.
Adding comments and docstrings to help students.
Finishing main function of find_orf module.
Working on incorporating ORF component.
Working on improving docstrings.
Working on tests to improve failure messages.
Adding .gitignore.

Fixing typos in docstrings.

Fixing a few 'and' -> 'an' typos.

Fixing test message.

Changing 'run_get_all_translations' to 'get_all_translations' in the
message reported by 'TestTranslateBaseClass.run_get_all_translations'.
Fixing typo in suggestion within README.
Adding more suggestions to the README.

Working on the README.

Adding a 'suggestions' section and some notes.

Removing unnecessary concatenation in main.

Removing unnecessary use of string concatenation ('+') when defining
`rna_seq` in the main code of `translate.py`. It will be good for
students to see that this is not necessary when wrapping a multiple
lines of strings with parentheses.
Adding message to main code.

Fixing class name error in test module.

I was accidentally using the class name `TestGetAllTranslations` twice
due to a copy-paste error. Changing the name of one to
`TestGetLongestPeptide`.

Fixing tests of get_longest_peptide.

There was a name conflict between what the testing method had for an
argument (expected_amino_acid_seq) and what calls of the method were
using (expected_result).  Updating the testing method to use the latter
and resolve the variable name conflict.
Adding some main code to translate.py.
Fixing link in README.

Working on README.

Removing missing images.
Adding README and LICENSE.
Adding more function placeholders and unittests.

Defining more placeholder functions.

These currently do nothing, and will have to be coded for the exercise.
Adding more unit tests.
Fleshing out tests of translate function.

Working on unit tests.

Writing a method of the test base class to test the `translate_sequence`
function.
Adding initial script and unit tests.
